[Operation] add willChangeValue() and didChangeValue()
items.body: Following on from the discussion on the swift-corelibs-dev mailing list, here's a PR to add `willChangeValue()` and `didChangeValue()` to `Operation`, in support of operations that are asynchronous from an operation queue.

items.title: SR-3662: Restore NSLog functionality on linux
SR-3362: Restore NSLog functionality on linux [Regression]
Make sure that os_log is turned off for both Darwin and Linux
items.body:
`os_log` calls back into CF on Darwin (for the ability to print `NSObject` types). However, this CF that we're testing in `swift-corelibs-foundation` is not the system one, and the types don't implement the expected forwarding protocols. Better to just disable this on all platforms.

Fixes SR-3703.
